HEADWORD: Donatory
<hw>Don"a*to*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Scots Law)</fld>
<def>A donee of the crown; one the whom, upon certain condition,
escheated property is made over.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

